# Git: commit and push after work

When you finish a task that touched the repo (code, config, or docs the user asked to change):

1. If source under `src/` changed, build the SharePoint package:
   `npx heft test --production; npx heft package-solution --production`
   (omit `--clean` on heft test to avoid Dropbox file locks). Skip if the task was docs-only or had no `src/` changes.
2. Run `git add .`
3. Run `git commit -m "<short imperative description of what changed>"` — do **not** ask whether to commit; use a clear message derived from the task.
4. Run `git push` to `origin` (current branch).

If `git status` shows nothing to commit, skip commit and push; otherwise always run these steps.

Do **not** wait for the user to say "push to sppkg" — package, commit, and push automatically after code changes unless the build fails (fix and retry before committing).

## Remote

`origin` must be:

`https://thestylecollectivenz@github.com/thestylecollectivenz/travelhub.git`

If `origin` is missing or points elsewhere, set it:

`git remote remove origin` (only if replacing), then  
`git remote add origin https://thestylecollectivenz@github.com/thestylecollectivenz/travelhub.git`

Do not wait for the user to approve commits or pushes for routine task completion.
